## Key Modification: OFMVC Implementation Fix

The original `main_clustering.py` (downloaded from https://github.com/AliReza000J/MVC-Time-series-Forecasting) had its view-weight optimization step commented out. 
This was identified and fixed — see Section 6.3 of the final report for full details.

**Summary of changes to `main_clustering.py`:**
- Added `learn_weights=False` parameter (default preserves original/FMVC behavior)
- Safe `beta` initialization before the iteration loop
- Uncommented and activated the view-weight update block (now runs only when `learn_weights=True`)
- Changed `return Final` to `return Final, w`


## How to Reproduce Results

1. Install dependencies: `pip install -r requirements.txt`
2. Place raw data files (see Data section below) in `Energy_Project/data/` and
   `Energy_Project_updated/data/raw/`
3. Run preprocessing: `python Energy_Project_updated/scripts/preprocess.py`
4. Run clustering scripts (OFMVC, FMVC, K-Means in `mvc_ts` environment;
   kShape requires a separate environment  (Environment Notes below)
5. Run forecasting scripts to reproduce SMAPE results

## Environment Notes

- All scripts run in conda environment `mvc_ts` (Python 3.10) EXCEPT:
- kShape clustering required a separate environment (`kshape_env`) due to a
  segmentation fault caused by a tslearn/NumPy version incompatibility in `mvc_ts`.
- See `requirements below for full dependency list.

